<paragraph blockId="10.[189,1399,700,1124]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
This subspecies was described based on an apparently large series of males collected by Wilmatte Porter Cockerell and Adan Rivera at Zamorano and Tegucigalpa on flowers of 
<taxonomicName authority="Jacq." authorityName="Jacq." box="[1124,1399,736,763]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Duranta" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="plumieri">
<emphasis box="[1124,1330,736,762]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Duranta plumieri</emphasis>
Jacq.
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[197,353,772,799]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Verbenaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Verbenaceae</taxonomicName>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Cockerell" box="[378,583,772,798]" firstAuthor="Cockerell" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" pagination="429 - 490" refId="ref20335" refString="Cockerell T. D. A. 1949. Bees from Central America, principally Honduras. Proceedings of the United States National Museum 98: 429 - 490. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00963801.98 - 3233.429" type="journal article" year="1949">Cockerell (1949)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned the type specimen was numbered “58887” but in the 
<collectionCode box="[189,282,809,835]" country="USA" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/142r-0w94" name="Smithsonian Institution, National Museum of Natural History" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="Museum">NMNH</collectionCode>
, two males with this number were found. One of them bears a label with the word “type” and the other is labeled “cotype”. The 
<typeStatus box="[599,702,844,870]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">holotype</typeStatus>
(
<figureCitation box="[719,790,844,871]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="10.[189,232,1966,1992]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,1470,1925]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[189,1398,1470,1925]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Fig. 6. Centris inermis pallidifrons Cockerell, 1949, holotype, ♂ (NMNH; USNM ENT 00534207). A. Frontal view. B. Habitus, lateral view. Scale bars: A = 1 mm; B = 2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3722964" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3722964/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
) has the following data label: Zamorano 
<collectingCountry box="[1284,1398,844,870]" name="Honduras" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Honduras</collectingCountry>
